1. PULPino

Aspect Details
Core PULPino (RI5CY, 32-bit RISC-V MCU)
Target Ultra-low-power IoT, edge devices
Strengths 4-stage pipeline, hardware loop support, low gate count (~30k gates)
Modifications Add ternary ALU + TWCET cycle counter + TGATE power gating
Ternary ISA Support TXNOR, TPOPCNT, TFMA, TGATE, TWCET
Area Overhead ~0.08 mm² (28nm)
Projected Energy/Query 4.2 µJ (with 100 tiles)
Projected Latency 720 ns
Best For Battery-powered edge AI, sensor fusion, wearables

Implementation Notes:

· PULPino's existing hardware loop and post-increment load/store accelerate packed ternary operations.
· The core's low gate count makes it ideal for 100-tile integration on a single die.
· Already verified in 40nm and 28nm processes.

---

2. NEORV32

Aspect Details
Core NEORV32 (32-bit RISC-V, highly configurable)
Target Research, education, FPGA, ASIC
Strengths Fully documented, modular, supports custom ISA extensions natively
Modifications Add ternary ALU + TWCET cycle counter + TGATE power gating
Ternary ISA Support TXNOR, TPOPCNT, TFMA, TGATE, TWCET
Area Overhead ~0.10 mm² (28nm)
Projected Energy/Query 3.7 µJ (with 100 tiles)
Projected Latency 680 ns
Best For FPGA prototyping, research, sovereign silicon development

Implementation Notes:

· NEORV32's CPU_EXTENSION_RISCV_C and CPU_EXTENSION_RISCV_Zba interfaces accept custom instructions with minimal overhead.
· The NEOVC system-on-chip includes optional TWCET and TGATE modules.
· Reference design is FPGA-ready (Lattice iCE40, Xilinx Artix-7, Intel Cyclone IV).

